                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.111 Habicht, Hermann: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-08">July 8,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received July 8—6:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1322. As Soviet authorities have finally agreed to issue exit visas to Mrs.
                    Hermann Habicht and son and to Mrs. Robert Magidoff, please authorize immediate
                    issuance immigration visas and allot one non-preference Soviet Union quota
                    number for issuance to minor son of Mrs. Habicht.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
